urlText: Rose Bay ferry wharf closed for maintenance
content:
From Monday 12 August to Wednesday 14 August, Rose Bay Ferry Wharf will be closed for essential repair work and planned maintenance.
 
All ferry services will be suspended during the closure.
 
Both Rose Bay (old and new) wharves will be closed during this time, however recreational vessels will still be able to access the boat ramp.
 
For alternative services please use route 323 buses to Edgecliff Station, then transfer to train for the city or route 324 and 325 buses to Edgecliff and then transfer to train or continue on bus to the city.

Please note - the 324 and 325 services operate via the western part of the CBD, so passengers will need to transfer at QVB if they need to travel to Circular Quay.

urlText: Major disruptions on L1 and L2/L3 light rail lines due to industrial action
content:
From Monday 22 to Friday 26 July, daily from 7.30am to 10.30am, and from 3.30pm to 6.30pm, L1 Dulwich Hill Line, L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line light rail services will be impacted due to industrial action: 
 
L1 Dulwich Hill Line:
 
Daily from 7.30am to 10.30am, and from 3.30pm to 6.30pm:
  • L1 light rail services will not run between Lilyfield and Dulwich Hill.
  • L1 light rail services will continue to run between Central Grand Concourse and Lilyfield at a reduced frequency.
L2 Randwick Line:
 
Daily from 7.30am to 10.30am, and from 3.30pm to 6.30pm:
  • L2 light rail services will not run between Circular Quay and Central Chalmers Street.
  • L2 light rail services will continue to run between Central Chalmers Street and Randwick at a reduced frequency.
L3 Kingsford Line:
 
Daily from 7.30am to 10.30am, and from 3.30pm to 6.30pm:
  • L3 light rail services will not run between Circular Quay and Juniors Kingsford.
Outside of these timings, L1, L2 and L3 light rail services will continue running; some services may run with delays:
  • Monday 22, Tuesday 23 and Wednesday 24 July: daily from 5am to 7.30am, from 10.30am to 3.30pm and from 6.30pm to 1am for L1 services, or 9pm for L2/L3 services due to pre-planned maintenance works. See the Trackwork News Story for more detailed service information.
  • Thursday 25 and Friday 26 July: daily from 5am to 7.30am, from 10.30am to 3.30pm and from 6.30pm to 1am.
Please use alternative transport, including replacement bus services, train services, regular bus services, or walking if able to.
 
See the news story for more detailed service information.
 
Light rail services will progressively resume from 10.30am, and again from 6.30pm daily and some services may run with delays.
 
Full L1, L2 and L3 light rail services will resume as per normal schedule from 5am Saturday 27 July.

urlText: Greenwich Point Wharf closed
content:
Monday 22 April until late 2024
 
Greenwich Point Wharf is being upgraded and will be closed to the public for around eight months, weather and site conditions permitting. Ferry passengers will need to use alternative transport during the wharf closure:
  • Use the existing 265 bus route which travels from Lane Cove to North Sydney via Greenwich, connecting with St Leonards and North Sydney train stations.
  • Additional bus services for the 265 route will be provided between Greenwich Point Wharf and Crows Nest, via St Leonards during weekdays and nights and over the weekends to offset the missing ferry services.
  • Captain Cook Cruises operates a commuter ferry service during peak travel times from Greenwich Wharf Bay Street. Please check their website for more information.
  • Allow extra travel time, listen to announcements and check information displays for service updates.
  • For more information on the Greenwich Point Wharf Upgrade please visit the Greenwich Point Wharf Upgrade page.

urlText: South Mosman Wharf closed for upgrades
content:
Monday 3 June until late 2024

South Mosman Wharf is being upgraded and will be closed to the public for around eight months, weather and site conditions permitting. Ferry passengers will need to use alternative transport during the wharf closure:

  • Public transport options include F2 and F6 ferry services from Mosman Bay Wharf.
  • Use the existing 111 bus service from Musgrave Street to Canrobert Street and change to the 230 bus from Avenue Road to Mosman Bay Wharf.
  • The 230 bus service from Military Road can also be used to connect to North Sydney and other destinations.
  • Allow extra travel time, listen to announcements, and check information displays for service updates.

urlText: L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line weeknight full closures due to maintenance
content:
Monday 22 to Wednesday 24 July
  • Nightly from 9pm to 1am, L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line light rail services will not run due to planned trackwork and maintenance works.
During this time, use alternative transport including:
  • Replacement bus services or regular bus services between Central Chalmers Street and Randwick or Juniors Kingsford,
  • Train services, regular bus services or walking if able to, between Circular Quay and Central Chalmers Street.
From Monday 22 to Friday 26 July, daily from 7.30am to 10.30am, and from 3.30pm to 6.30pm, L1 Dulwich Hill Line, L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line light rail services will be impacted due to industrial action. Buses will replace most light rail services during this time. See the Major disruptions News Story for more detailed service information.
 
Replacement bus services:
 
Replacement bus services will run every 10 to 15 minutes from 9pm to 1am nightly. These times may vary depending on road traffic.
 
Replacement buses will not stop at the following locations:
  • Surry Hills (towards Central and Randwick or Juniors Kingsford)
    - Use the alternative stop at Central Chalmers Street (approx. 8 minute walk),
  • Wansey Road (towards Central)
    - Use the alternative stop at Royal Randwick (approx. 12 minute walk),
  • UNSW High Street (towards Central and Randwick)
    - Use the alternative stop at Randwick (approx. 10 minute walk).
  • See the news story for more detailed service information.
  • Allow extra trave time, and plan ahead using the Trip Planner to see if your travel is affected, or to find alternative transport options.
